connecting places hundreds
of kilometers afar, at least

00:35:20.050 --> 00:35:23.720 align:middle line:90%
an hour's walk is needed.

00:35:23.720 --> 00:35:29.270 align:middle line:84%
The place is called Infiernillo,
meaning "little hell,"

00:35:29.270 --> 00:35:32.180 align:middle line:84%
and the name exactly
sums up what the natives

00:35:32.180 --> 00:35:33.816 align:middle line:90%
think of this tunnel.

00:35:33.816 --> 00:35:37.008 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:35:37.008 --> 00:35:37.920 align:middle line:90%


00:35:37.920 --> 00:35:42.150 align:middle line:84%
The entrance to the canal is
about seven meters underground,

00:35:42.150 --> 00:35:45.150 align:middle line:84%
and it can be reached by
crossing a cleft between two

00:35:45.150 --> 00:35:46.245 align:middle line:90%
gigantic rocks.

00:35:46.245 --> 00:35:48.830 align:middle line:90%


00:35:48.830 --> 00:35:52.550 align:middle line:84%
When Ruzo used to work here,
Manuel did lower himself

00:35:52.550 --> 00:35:56.410 align:middle line:84%
down various meters,
but the archaeologist

00:35:56.410 --> 00:35:58.720 align:middle line:84%
feared for his safety
and prevented him

00:35:58.720 --> 00:36:00.340 align:middle line:90%
from continuing the descent.

00:36:00.340 --> 00:36:03.833 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:36:03.833 --> 00:36:11.830 align:middle line:90%


00:36:11.830 --> 00:36:14.320 align:middle line:84%
To reach the entrance,
it is important to have

00:36:14.320 --> 00:36:15.694 align:middle line:90%
mountain gear.

00:36:15.694 --> 00:36:19.012 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:36:19.012 --> 00:36:23.290 align:middle line:90%


00:36:23.290 --> 00:36:25.480 align:middle line:84%
Unfortunately, the
heavy rainfalls

00:36:25.480 --> 00:36:28.750 align:middle line:84%
which have hit the meseta
have brought mud and silt,

00:36:28.750 --> 00:36:31.120 align:middle line:90%
which now block the entrance.

00:36:31.120 --> 00:36:33.730 align:middle line:84%
