00:38:14.600 --> 00:38:17.360 align:middle line:84%
and even right
season of the year.

00:38:17.360 --> 00:38:23.830 align:middle line:84%
Lacking these prerequisites, the
sculptures are indecipherable.

00:38:23.830 --> 00:38:27.570 align:middle line:84%
This rock was called the
African Lion by the scholar,

00:38:27.570 --> 00:38:29.740 align:middle line:84%
and one can guess
the profile only

00:38:29.740 --> 00:38:32.230 align:middle line:84%
when looking from a
certain perspective,

00:38:32.230 --> 00:38:35.440 align:middle line:90%
exactly as explained by Ruzo.

00:38:35.440 --> 00:38:40.930 align:middle line:84%
If viewed from other angles, it
shows no comprehensible shape.

00:38:40.930 --> 00:38:43.870 align:middle line:84%
Identifying the sculptures
is made even more difficult

00:38:43.870 --> 00:38:47.170 align:middle line:84%
by natural erosion due to
the enormous amount of time

00:38:47.170 --> 00:38:49.920 align:middle line:90%
passed since their creation.

00:38:49.920 --> 00:38:53.530 align:middle line:84%
The period surmised by Ruzo
dates back much further

00:38:53.530 --> 00:38:58.260 align:middle line:84%
than the common accepted time
to extremely ancient eras

00:38:58.260 --> 00:39:02.440 align:middle line:84%
over 10,000 years
ago, an age which

00:39:02.440 --> 00:39:05.470 align:middle line:84%
would have certainly
transformed tools or handiwork

00:39:05.470 --> 00:39:09.100 align:middle line:84%
left by the mysterious
sculptors to dust,

00:39:09.100 --> 00:39:11.680 align:middle line:84%
making any test currently
available to date

00:39:11.680 --> 00:39:14.051 align:middle line:84%
the drawings
practically useless.

00:39:14.051 --> 00:39:17.418 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:39:17.418 --> 00:39:20.785 align:middle line:90%


00:39:20.785 --> 00:39:23.190 align:middle line:90%
>> [SPEAKING SPANISH]

00:39:23.190 --> 00:39:26.850 align:middle line:84%
>> This is Marcahuasi, and this
is the Monument for Humanity.

00:39:26.850 --> 00:39:29.616 align:middle line:90%


00:39:29.616 --> 00:39:30.990 align:middle line:84%
We have come here
so that you can

00:39:30.990 --> 00:39:35.430 align:middle line:84%
learn about it and the other
drawings which are here.

00:39:35.430 --> 00:39:38.730 align:middle line:84%
>> The most famous work at
Marcahuasi is the Monument

00:39:38.730 --> 00:39:39.980 align:middle line:90%
for Humanity.

00:39:39.980 --> 00:39:44.010 align:middle line:84%
Ruzo had come up with this name,
but its existence was already

00:39:44.010 --> 00:39:47.400 align:middle line:84%
known by the indigenous
population for a long time,

00:39:47.400 --> 00:39:51.830 align:middle line:84%
and they called it
the Head of the Inca.

00:39:51.830 --> 00:39:55.970 align:middle line:84%
It is 25 meters tall
and is very eroded,

00:39:55.970 --> 00:40:00.420 align:middle line:84%
but the profile
is clearly human.

00:40:00.420 --> 00:40:02.570 align:middle line:84%
Ruzo discovered
that, by glancing

00:40:02.570 --> 00:40:05.960 align:middle line:84%
at it from different angles
and light conditions,

00:40:05.960 --> 00:40:11.060 align:middle line:84%
other faces of various sizes
belonging to all human races

00:40:11.060 --> 00:40:13.850 align:middle line:90%
appeared on its surface.

00:40:13.850 --> 00:40:20.720 align:middle line:84%
That's how it gained its current
name, Monumento a la Humanidad.

00:40:20.720 --> 00:40:23.570 align:middle line:84%
Other drawings can be
seen from the plateau.

00:40:23.570 --> 00:40:25.520 align:middle line:90%
Some are clearly identifiable.

00:40:25.520 --> 00:40:28.747 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:40:28.747 --> 00:40:29.670 align:middle line:90%


00:40:29.670 --> 00:40:32.670 align:middle line:84%
Others are hidden in
the mysterious landscape

00:40:32.670 --> 00:40:35.640 align:middle line:84%
of the meseta, awaiting
the ideal conditions

00:40:35.640 --> 00:40:40.440 align:middle line:84%
to unveil themselves to
the eyes of observers.

00:40:40.440 --> 00:40:44.520 align:middle line:84%
But many archaeologists did not
agree on the artificial origin

00:40:44.520 --> 00:40:46.080 align:middle line:90%
of the sculptures.

00:40:46.080 --> 00:40:49.020 align:middle line:84%
They claim that they were
created by natural erosion

00:40:49.020 --> 00:40:51.440 align:middle line:90%
and weather conditions.

00:40:51.440 --> 00:40:53.610 align:middle line:84%
Fully convinced
of his discovery,

00:40:53.610 --> 00:40:56.120 align:middle line:84%
Ruzo invited
important researchers

00:40:56.120 --> 00:40:58.040 align:middle line:84%
to visit and study
the sculptures

00:40:58.040 --> 00:41:00.560 align:middle line:90%
and data he had collected.

00:41:00.560 --> 00:41:05.240 align:middle line:84%
The German Albert Giesecke,
the Frenchman Marcel Homet,

00:41:05.240 --> 00:41:08.390 align:middle line:84%
the Austrian archaeologist
Hans Schindler Bellamy,

00:41:08.390 --> 00:41:10.760 align:middle line:84%
and the Englishman
Peter Allen all

00:41:10.760 --> 00:41:14.010 align:middle line:84%
agreed with the theories
supported by Ruzo.

00:41:14.010 --> 00:41:17.300 align:middle line:84%
Allen, personally, visited
the Marcahuasi sculptures

00:41:17.300 --> 00:41:19.850 align:middle line:84%
and was so impressed
he said, the fact

00:41:19.850 --> 00:41:25.410 align:middle line:84%
that they have this peculiarity
implies an uncommon technique.

00:41:25.410 --> 00:41:28.270 align:middle line:84%
Once more, the science
world was divided

00:41:28.270 --> 00:41:31.430 align:middle line:90%
into two opposite stands.

00:41:31.430 --> 00:41:32.750 align:middle line:90%
Who was right?

00:41:32.750 --> 00:41:36.110 align:middle line:84%
And once more, the
usual question arose.

00:41:36.110 --> 00:41:39.710 align:middle line:84%
Did the people who inhabited
the meseta in ancient times

00:41:39.710 --> 00:41:42.200 align:middle line:84%
remember the origin of
the finds in a place

00:41:42.200 --> 00:41:44.600 align:middle line:90%
the Incas considered sacred?

00:41:44.600 --> 00:41:47.780 align:middle line:10%
Pedro Cieza de León,
Spanish reporter with

00:41:47.780 --> 00:41:51.740 align:middle line:10%
the conquistadores, asked them
if they knew who had created

00:41:51.740 --> 00:41:54.920 align:middle line:10%
the strange shapes which
were on the plateau.

00:41:54.920 --> 00:41:57.200 align:middle line:10%
They replied that
they belong to men

00:41:57.200 --> 00:42:01.350 align:middle line:10%
who came from afar,
white-skinned foreigners

00:42:01.350 --> 00:42:02.150 align:middle line:10%
with a beard.

00:42:02.150 --> 00:42:05.629 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:42:05.629 --> 00:42:35.990 align:middle line:90%


00:42:35.990 --> 00:42:41.960 align:middle line:84%
The imposing ruins of Chavín de
Huántar are 3,200 meters high,

00:42:41.960 --> 00:42:45.320 align:middle line:84%
lying between the
mountains of southern Peru.

00:42:45.320 --> 00:42:48.150 align:middle line:84%
They have been attributed
to the Chavín culture,

00:42:48.150 --> 00:42:50.840 align:middle line:84%
one of the most important
in ancient Peru,

00:42:50.840 --> 00:42:53.780 align:middle line:84%
considered the cultural route
of the subsequent Andean

00:42:53.780 --> 00:42:56.100 align:middle line:90%
civilizations.

00:42:56.100 --> 00:42:59.840 align:middle line:84%
This culture developed
suddenly in 1200 BC,

00:42:59.840 --> 00:43:03.290 align:middle line:84%
and its influence spread to
coastlines far from Peru.

00:43:03.290 --> 00:43:05.810 align:middle line:90%


00:43:05.810 --> 00:43:07.970 align:middle line:84%
The entire complex
of buildings is

00:43:07.970 --> 00:43:11.090 align:middle line:84%
set towards east
west, amongst which

00:43:11.090 --> 00:43:14.960 align:middle line:84%
the large temple, which
overlooks the entire site.

00:43:14.960 --> 00:43:19.520 align:middle line:84%
It is called El Castillo and is
built with various sized stone

00:43:19.520 --> 00:43:23.540 align:middle line:84%
blocks with a more or less
regular weight and shape.

00:43:23.540 --> 00:43:26.690 align:middle line:84%
The walls were covered
with large, stone slabs,

00:43:26.690 --> 00:43:29.675 align:middle line:84%
sometimes carved in the
characteristic Chavín style.

00:43:29.675 --> 00:43:32.780 align:middle line:90%


00:43:32.780 --> 00:43:35.610 align:middle line:84%
Similar carvings can be seen
on the columns of the temple

00:43:35.610 --> 00:43:36.676 align:middle line:90%
portal.

00:43:36.676 --> 00:43:40.078 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:43:40.078 --> 00:43:43.980 align:middle line:90%


00:43:43.980 --> 00:43:47.760 align:middle line:84%
And on several stones slabs
of the ancient round square.

00:43:47.760 --> 00:43:51.120 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:43:51.120 --> 00:43:57.380 align:middle line:90%


00:43:57.380 --> 00:44:01.460 align:middle line:84%
The walls of the Castillo were
adorned with over 200 stone

00:44:01.460 --> 00:44:04.280 align:middle line:90%
heads, called hollow heads.

00:44:04.280 --> 00:44:07.940 align:middle line:84%
Currently, only one has
remained fixed in place.

00:44:07.940 --> 00:44:12.632 align:middle line:84%
The others have been transferred
to the small Chavín museum.

00:44:12.632 --> 00:44:16.230 align:middle line:10%
>> [SPEAKING SPANISH]

00:44:16.230 --> 00:44:17.030 align:middle line:10%
>> Yes.

00:44:17.030 --> 00:44:18.550 align:middle line:10%
Here in the exhibition
hall, we have

00:44:18.550 --> 00:44:23.600 align:middle line:10%
heads with proud faces,
astonished faces.

00:44:23.600 --> 00:44:26.000 align:middle line:84%
Research claims that
these hollow heads

00:44:26.000 --> 00:44:28.250 align:middle line:84%
show people who are
in a trance state,

00:44:28.250 --> 00:44:29.750 align:middle line:90%
in a hallucinatory state.

00:44:29.750 --> 00:44:32.510 align:middle line:90%


00:44:32.510 --> 00:44:34.790 align:middle line:84%
These expressions would
terrify the visitor

00:44:34.790 --> 00:44:36.560 align:middle line:90%
who came to this area.

00:44:36.560 --> 00:44:40.130 align:middle line:84%
The hollow heads were stuck,
fixed to the walls of the main

00:44:40.130 --> 00:44:42.490 align:middle line:90%
Chavín temple.

00:44:42.490 --> 00:44:46.360 align:middle line:84%
>> The Chavín population
worshiped the jaguar god,

00:44:46.360 --> 00:44:50.320 align:middle line:84%
and its religion originated
from the atomic bond between man

00:44:50.320 --> 00:44:54.870 align:middle line:84%
and the forest,
a religion which,

00:44:54.870 --> 00:44:57.540 align:middle line:84%
as the museum's
director explains,

00:44:57.540 --> 00:45:00.810 align:middle line:84%
terrified its believers with
practices which probably

00:45:00.810 --> 00:45:04.290 align:middle line:84%
utilized hallucinogenic
substances.

00:45:04.290 --> 00:45:07.440 align:middle line:84%
It seems strange, however,
that a population with such

00:45:07.440 --> 00:45:11.160 align:middle line:84%
a primitive religion had the
knowledge to build the imposing

00:45:11.160 --> 00:45:14.430 align:middle line:90%
Chavín structures.

00:45:14.430 --> 00:45:17.820 align:middle line:84%
Could it be, perhaps, that
the Chavín people had simply

00:45:17.820 --> 00:45:22.350 align:middle line:84%
occupied preexisting structures
built by a population which had

00:45:22.350 --> 00:45:26.190 align:middle line:84%
disappeared and had
more advanced knowledge?

00:45:26.190 --> 00:45:29.730 align:middle line:84%
The Castillo is also
called Old Temple,

00:45:29.730 --> 00:45:33.270 align:middle line:84%
but by looking carefully at
it, rather than a temple,

00:45:33.270 --> 00:45:35.940 align:middle line:90%
it looks like a giant strongbox.

00:45:35.940 --> 00:45:39.630 align:middle line:84%
Its massive walls, in fact,
do not have any windows,

00:45:39.630 --> 00:45:43.378 align:middle line:84%
and inside, there are
no large worship holes.

00:45:43.378 --> 00:45:46.864 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:45:46.864 --> 00:45:49.860 align:middle line:90%


00:45:49.860 --> 00:45:53.370 align:middle line:84%
Underground, one of the
galleries leads to a small,

00:45:53.370 --> 00:45:57.060 align:middle line:84%
cross-shaped room, where the
most valuable and sacred Chavín

00:45:57.060 --> 00:45:58.908 align:middle line:90%
work stands out.

00:45:58.908 --> 00:46:02.394 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:46:02.394 --> 00:46:03.390 align:middle line:90%


00:46:03.390 --> 00:46:07.300 align:middle line:84%
A granite monolith 4
and 1/2 meters high

00:46:07.300 --> 00:46:10.570 align:middle line:84%
with a monstrous, carved,
anthropomorphic figure

00:46:10.570 --> 00:46:13.450 align:middle line:90%
revealing animal features.

00:46:13.450 --> 00:46:18.010 align:middle line:84%
The style is typical of
the Chavín population

00:46:18.010 --> 00:46:21.190 align:middle line:84%
and represents the highest
divinity of that ancient

00:46:21.190 --> 00:46:25.950 align:middle line:90%
culture, the jaguar god.

00:46:25.950 --> 00:46:29.590 align:middle line:84%
The monolith is called
El Lanzón, the Spear,

00:46:29.590 --> 00:46:32.850 align:middle line:84%
and neither the passageway
leading to it nor the narrow

00:46:32.850 --> 00:46:36.000 align:middle line:84%
hole where it is placed
were suitable to hold large,

00:46:36.000 --> 00:46:38.760 align:middle line:90%
worshipping crowds.

00:46:38.760 --> 00:46:41.200 align:middle line:84%
But from a religious
point of view,

00:46:41.200 --> 00:46:43.440 align:middle line:90%
there is no sense in this.

00:46:43.440 --> 00:46:46.110 align:middle line:84%
Usually, a divinity
would be visited

00:46:46.110 --> 00:46:51.270 align:middle line:84%
by a large number of people
to be honored and worshiped.

00:46:51.270 --> 00:46:54.450 align:middle line:84%
Its life-size reproduction
can be admired in the garden

00:46:54.450 --> 00:46:59.190 align:middle line:84%
of the Chavín Museum
and leveled over a wall.

00:46:59.190 --> 00:47:02.160 align:middle line:84%
The aspect of the
jaguar god incredibly

00:47:02.160 --> 00:47:05.190 align:middle line:84%
resembles the
Viracocha depictions.

00:47:05.190 --> 00:47:09.750 align:middle line:10%
Stumpy legs, large belly, and
large head out of proportion

00:47:09.750 --> 00:47:11.160 align:middle line:10%
to his body.

00:47:11.160 --> 00:47:14.970 align:middle line:84%
Is this only a
casual coincidence?

00:47:14.970 --> 00:47:18.120 align:middle line:10%
Could it be another trace of
the passage of the mythical

00:47:18.120 --> 00:47:19.782 align:middle line:10%
Viracochas?

00:47:19.782 --> 00:47:23.226 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:47:23.226 --> 00:47:24.210 align:middle line:90%


00:47:24.210 --> 00:47:27.810 align:middle line:84%
It is possible to access an
intricate, underground network

00:47:27.810 --> 00:47:33.180 align:middle line:84%
of corridors, holes, narrow
tunnels, air ducts, and a water

00:47:33.180 --> 00:47:36.810 align:middle line:84%
canalization from the open
entrances at the top of the Old

00:47:36.810 --> 00:47:41.220 align:middle line:84%
Temple and from others
spread in various points.

00:47:41.220 --> 00:47:44.280 align:middle line:84%
These are currently
unusable, obstructed

00:47:44.280 --> 00:47:46.740 align:middle line:90%
by debris and cave-ins.

00:47:46.740 --> 00:47:50.340 align:middle line:84%
But once, they connected the
waters of the two rivers where

00:47:50.340 --> 00:47:53.540 align:middle line:84%
Chavín de Huántar
nestles in the middle.

00:47:53.540 --> 00:47:56.970 align:middle line:84%
Huanchecsa overlooks
Chavín and Mosna,

00:47:56.970 --> 00:47:58.950 align:middle line:90%
which is at a lower height.

00:47:58.950 --> 00:48:01.290 align:middle line:10%
The water descended
from Huanchecsa,

00:48:01.290 --> 00:48:04.080 align:middle line:10%
and it would fill the
large, sunken square

00:48:04.080 --> 00:48:07.050 align:middle line:10%
in front of the Castillo
through its channels

00:48:07.050 --> 00:48:09.810 align:middle line:10%
to finally flow in the Mosna.

00:48:09.810 --> 00:48:13.530 align:middle line:10%
Could it be that such a
sophisticated water network

00:48:13.530 --> 00:48:19.080 align:middle line:10%
only had a ritual purpose, and
could the Chavín underground be

00:48:19.080 --> 00:48:23.070 align:middle line:10%
part of the legendary network of
tunnels which connected ancient

00:48:23.070 --> 00:48:26.550 align:middle line:10%
sites of a forgotten past?

00:48:26.550 --> 00:48:30.210 align:middle line:84%
Mr. Lopez, archaeologist
in charge of Chavín,

00:48:30.210 --> 00:48:33.630 align:middle line:84%
states that there truly are
underground tunnels which

00:48:33.630 --> 00:48:37.350 align:middle line:84%
depart from Chavín towards
other unexplored settlements

00:48:37.350 --> 00:48:40.374 align:middle line:90%
of the surrounding mountains.

00:48:40.374 --> 00:48:43.000 align:middle line:10%
>> [SPEAKING SPANISH]

00:48:43.000 --> 00:48:44.550 align:middle line:10%


00:48:44.550 --> 00:48:48.180 align:middle line:10%
>> The ancient Chavín population
mentioned tunnels which

00:48:48.180 --> 00:48:51.060 align:middle line:10%
connected an area
northeast of here,

00:48:51.060 --> 00:48:53.910 align:middle line:10%
about 2 kilometers away
in the higher mountains.

00:48:53.910 --> 00:48:56.760 align:middle line:90%


00:48:56.760 --> 00:48:59.310 align:middle line:84%
The ancient Chavín
people spoke of this,

00:48:59.310 --> 00:49:03.300 align:middle line:84%
so it is likely this
connection truly exists.

00:49:03.300 --> 00:49:06.350 align:middle line:84%
>> For the first time,
video cameras have entered

00:49:06.350 --> 00:49:10.620 align:middle line:84%
the tunnels in Chavín, some
of which are still unexplored.

00:49:10.620 --> 00:49:14.150 align:middle line:90%


00:49:14.150 --> 00:49:17.630 align:middle line:84%
It's a difficult path,
and the presence of bats

00:49:17.630 --> 00:49:20.630 align:middle line:90%
makes it even less accessible.

00:49:20.630 --> 00:49:23.720 align:middle line:84%
The network of underground
tunnels is intricate,

00:49:23.720 --> 00:49:26.570 align:middle line:84%
and the conjecture that
the whole structure only

00:49:26.570 --> 00:49:31.250 align:middle line:84%
had a religious purpose is
increasingly less acceptable.

00:49:31.250 --> 00:49:35.390 align:middle line:84%
Did the Chavín population
really build the complex,

00:49:35.390 --> 00:49:39.620 align:middle line:84%
or did it simply settle
in buildings it had found,

00:49:39.620 --> 00:49:42.950 align:middle line:84%
readapting these to
its requirements,

00:49:42.950 --> 00:49:45.710 align:middle line:84%
buildings constructed by
a population which had

00:49:45.710 --> 00:49:49.190 align:middle line:84%
disappeared and with
more advanced knowledge?

00:49:49.190 --> 00:49:52.910 align:middle line:84%
The American archaeologist
Ephraim George Squier,

00:49:52.910 --> 00:49:58.220 align:middle line:84%
in his book "Peru, Incidents
of Travel and Explorations

00:49:58.220 --> 00:50:02.150 align:middle line:84%
in the Lands of Incas"
published in 1887,

00:50:02.150 --> 00:50:05.360 align:middle line:84%
believed that two, distinct
cultural eras existed

00:50:05.360 --> 00:50:11.570 align:middle line:84%
in Peru's history, one extremely
ancient with the most advanced

00:50:11.570 --> 00:50:15.860 align:middle line:84%
scientific knowledge, and
the other much more recent

00:50:15.860 --> 00:50:20.150 align:middle line:84%
like that of the Incas with
a lower cultural level.

00:50:20.150 --> 00:50:23.420 align:middle line:84%
According to Squier, an
extremely hard to calculate

00:50:23.420 --> 00:50:26.630 align:middle line:84%
span of time, but
certainly broad,

00:50:26.630 --> 00:50:29.210 align:middle line:84%
passed between
these two cultures.

00:50:29.210 --> 00:50:31.670 align:middle line:84%
He is also convinced
that the ancient

00:50:31.670 --> 00:50:34.370 align:middle line:84%
and sophisticated
Peruvian finds are

00:50:34.370 --> 00:50:38.090 align:middle line:84%
evidence of an advanced
technology, heritage

00:50:38.090 --> 00:50:41.720 align:middle line:90%
of a forgotten humanity.

00:50:41.720 --> 00:50:45.760 align:middle line:84%
The tunnels unwind for
still unknown distances,

00:50:45.760 --> 00:50:48.650 align:middle line:84%
also due to the danger
of covering them.

00:50:48.650 --> 00:50:52.700 align:middle line:84%
Many are damaged or obstructed,
and in fact, in the end,

00:50:52.700 --> 00:50:55.670 align:middle line:84%
it becomes impossible
to continue.

00:50:55.670 --> 00:50:59.150 align:middle line:84%
Luckily, there are side
exits, which suddenly emerge

00:50:59.150 --> 00:51:01.700 align:middle line:90%
from the large, main square.

00:51:01.700 --> 00:51:05.420 align:middle line:84%
